      "source": [
        "## Step 3. Roberta Pretrained Model\n",
        "\n",
        "#### - Use a model trained of a large corpus of data\n",
        "#### - Transformer model accounts for the words but also the context related to other words\n",
        "\n",
        "#### No, RoBERTa is not the same thing as Hugging Face.\n",
        "#### RoBERTa is a specific AI model created by Facebook AI (now Meta).Hugging Face is an open-source AI platform that hosts and provides code for thousands of different models, including RoBERTa.\n",
        "#### Here is the difference between the two:RoBERTa (The Model): A powerful natural language processing (NLP) model built by Facebook researchers. It is an optimized version of Google's original BERT model.Hugging Face (The Platform): A company and repository where developers can download, share, and use pre-trained AI models."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "QVaquG_VDtg2"
      }
    },
